## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Pages and components
  - ExportsDashboardComponent
  - ExportGeneratorPanel
  - ExportSettingsPanel (branding, signature block, timestamp granularity)
  - ExportHistoryList
  - BillingInfoPanel (export credits)
  - DecisionDetailView
  - SuccessConfirmationPage
  - LoadingScreen
- UI elements
  - Brandable header with breadcrumbs
  - Toggle switches for including attachments
  - Multi-select for decisions (bulk export)
  - Format picker (PDF/CSV) with clear icons
  - Branding controls: upload logo, color picker defaults, domain mapping field
  - PDF Viewer / inline preview for templates (optional)
- State management
  - Centralized export state (selected decisions, format, options)
  - Async export job tracking with polling or event-driven updates
- Accessibility
  - Keyboard navigable, ARIA roles for dynamic sections
- Performance
  - Debounced search/filter for decision lists
  - Lazy load heavy attachments when exporting

### Backend
- Data models (extend existing)
  - DecisionCard(id, projectId, options[], comments[], approvals[], auditTrail[], attachments[], timestamps[])
  - ExportJob(id, projectId, userId, decisionIds[], format, includeAttachments, branding, signatureRequested, status, createdAt, updatedAt, downloadUrl)
  - AuditLogEntry(id, decisionId, action, performedBy, timestamp, details)
  - BrandingProfile(id, studioId, logoUrl, colorHex, domain, font, headerMarkdown)
  - PDFTemplate(id, name, htmlTemplate, cssOverrides, lastModified)
- APIs
  - POST /exports/create
    - Body: { projectId, decisionIds[], format(PDF/CSV), includeAttachments, brandingProfileId, signatureRequested, coverOptions }
    - Returns: jobId, status
  - GET /exports/{jobId}/status
    - Returns: { status: processing|ready|failed, progress, downloadUrl }
  - GET /exports/{jobId}/download
    - Returns: file content with correct Content-Type
  - GET /branding/profiles
    - List studio branding profiles
  - POST /branding/profiles
    - Create/update branding profile (logo, color, domain)
  - GET /decision-logs/{decisionId}/audit
    - Return full audit trail for a decision
  - POST /decision-logs/template
    - Upload/manage PDF template
- Database tables
  - decisions (existing)
  - exports (new)
  - export_history (new)
  - branding_profiles (new)
  - audit_logs (existing or extended)
  - pdf_templates (new)
- File storage
  - Attachments and exported PDFs stored in object storage (S3-like) with signed access URLs
- Validation
  - Validate decisionIds belong to the same project
  - Validate format compatibility and attachments size
  - Validate branding profile is active and assets exist
- Security
  - Auth: User authentication; authorization ensuring only project members and studio branding owners can export
  - Resource access: project-scoped tokens/permissions
  - Data integrity: audit trails immutable post-creation for export logs
- Reliability
  - Idempotent export creation when re-triggered with same parameters
  - Retry strategy for transient storage or PDF rendering failures
- Observability
  - Structured logs for export job lifecycle
  - Metrics: export_duration, success_rate, average_attachment_size

### Integration
- Data flow
  - Decision Cards feed into ExportJob as chosen decisionIds
  - Audit logs feed into PDF/Audit sections
  - BrandingProfile is applied to the PDF template and export metadata
  - Attachments included conditionally per user setting
  - Export History records every attempt with status and download URL
- UI integration
  - Exports page orchestrates ExportGeneratorPanel, ExportHistoryList, and BillingInfoPanel
  - Decision Detail Page pulls in DecisionCard data, audit trails, and attachments
  - Success page is shown after ExportJob reaches ready status or a client-approved action completes
  - Loading/Processing Page is shown during long-running export generation
- PDF Template Rendering
  - Server-side renderer compiles brandable HTML/CSS into PDF
  - Cover page, decision option visuals, audit log, and attachments appendix render deterministically
  - Optional digital signature block appended if signatureRequested

---

## User Experience Flow

1. User navigates to Exports & Decision Logs.
2. User selects one or more decisions (single or bulk) to export.
3. User chooses export format: PDF or CSV.
4. User toggles Include Attachments as needed.
5. User selects Branding Profile (studio branding) and optional signature block; optionally specify a custom domain for client links.
6. User reviews export settings and credits; initiates export.
7. System creates an ExportJob, returns jobId; user sees a processing state on the page and a loading indicator.
8. Backend renders the PDF/CSV using the PDF Template with full audit history and attachments; stores file and updates job status to ready.
9. User is notified (in-page confirmation or via success page) and can download the file or view the export history entry.
10. If signed PDFs are requested, the system appends a signed block and provides a signed PDF download option.
11. User can view Export History, including status, timestamp, and download links; billing/credits are updated accordingly.

Edge cases:
- If export fails, show a friendly error with retry option and guidance.
- If branding assets are missing, fallback to default appearance with a prominent warning.
- If decisions span multiple projects, enforce project-scoped export to avoid cross-project data leakage.

---

## Technical Specifications

- Data Models: 
  - DecisionCard: id, projectId, title, options[], comments[], approvals[], attachments[], auditTrail[], createdAt, updatedAt
  - ExportJob: id, projectId, userId, decisionIds[], format, includeAttachments, brandingProfileId, signatureRequested, status, progress, createdAt, updatedAt, downloadUrl
  - BrandingProfile: id, studioId, name, logoUrl, colorHex, domain, font, headerMarkdown, isActive
  - AuditLogEntry: id, decisionId, action, performedBy, timestamp, details
  - PdfTemplate: id, name, htmlTemplate, cssOverrides, lastModified
  - ExportHistory: id, exportJobId, userId, projectId, decisionCount, format, includeAttachments, brandingProfileId, signed, status, createdAt, completedAt, downloadUrl
- API Endpoints:
  - POST /exports/create
  - GET /exports/{jobId}/status
  - GET /exports/{jobId}/download
  - GET /branding/profiles
  - POST /branding/profiles
  - GET /decision-logs/{decisionId}/audit
  - POST /decision-logs/template
- Security:
  - JWT/OIDC authentication; authorize by project membership and branding access
  - Role awareness: viewer vs editor vs admin for exports and branding
  - Audit: immutable export history entries; sensitive data redaction policies as needed
- Validation:
  - Ensure all selected decisions belong to the same project
  - Validate that brandingProfile isActive and assets exist
  - Validate file size limits for attachments when exporting
  - Validate domain mapping for custom client links
- Data Persistence:
  - Relational DB with foreign keys: exports.brandingProfileId -> branding_profiles.id; export_history.exportJobId -> exports.id; decisions linked via decisionIds[]
- External/Internal Services:
  - PDF rendering engine (HTML/CSS to PDF)
  - Object storage for PDFs/attachments
  - Optional digital signature service for signed PDFs
- Performance:
  - Asynchronous export rendering; progress tracking
  - Efficient streaming of large attachments
- Observability:
  - Metrics: export_duration_ms, export_status_counts, attachments_included, branding_profile_usage
  - Traces for PDF rendering steps
- Accessibility and UX:
  - Clear status indicators (processing, ready, failed)
  - Keyboard accessible controls, descriptive aria-labels
  - Consistent focus states and high-contrast controls

---

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Users can select one or more decisions and generate a PDF or CSV export including full history and optional attachments.
- [ ] Export settings allow applying branding, including a logo, color scheme, and optional domain for client links.
- [ ] Exports appear in the Export History with correct status transitions (processing -> ready) and downloadable links.
- [ ] Signed PDF option is available and produces a legally suitable signed document; the system provides a signed PDF download path.
- [ ] PDF template renders with a cover page, decision visuals, audit trail, and attachments appendix; must be brandable per BrandingProfile.
- [ ] Decision Detail Page accurately reflects options, comments, approval state, history, attachments, and supports actions (share, export, create follow-up task).
- [ ] Centralized error handling surfaces user-friendly messages and recovery actions; UI remains responsive during failures.
- [ ] Billing info shows export credits usage and remaining balance for paid plans.
- [ ] All endpoints are secured with proper authentication and project-scoped authorization; data isolation between studios/projects is enforced.
- [ ] UI adheres to the design system, color palette, typography, spacing, and interactive behaviors described.

