=== TASK ===
# Exports & Decision Logs

## Overview
Develop a complete, end-to-end module for Archject that enables branded exports and authoritative decision logs. This includes generating downloadable decision logs (PDF/CSV), export history, and signed PDF options suitable for legal use; an audit-logged Decision Log with full history and attachments; a core Decision Objects & Approval Workflow; robust error handling and validation; branding customization including client-facing links; a brandable PDF template for decision logs; and supportive UI pages (Success/Confirmation, Decision Detail, and Loading/Processing). The system should be highly usable for design studios, support secure exports, provide clear audit trails, and integrate smoothly with the existing Archject core (Decision Cards, Options, Comments, Approvals, Attachments, and Audit Trails). No external APIs are required for this task.

---

## Page Description (Full Detail)

What this page is:
- Exports & Decision Logs page: a centralized workspace where users can generate downloadable approval packs, view export history, configure export settings, and access signed PDF options for legal use. This page ties to Audit Logs & Export (Decision Log), Decision Objects & Approval Workflow (Core), Error Handling & Validation, Branding & Custom Client Links, and the Decision Log PDF Template.

Goals:
- Allow users to generate and download decision logs in PDF and CSV formats, including full history, attachments, and firm branding.
- Provide export history with status indicators (processing, ready) and direct download links.
- Offer signed PDF options for legal use (where applicable, e.g., digital signature blocks, timestamping).
- Present an extensible export flow that respects branding, timestamps, and attachment inclusion.
- Display export credits/billing information for paid plans.
- Maintain a consistent, branded UI that matches the project’s design system.

Connected features and UI behavior:
- Audit Logs & Export (Decision Log): Generate authoritative, time-stamped logs with full history, attachments, and firm branding; export in PDF/CSV; signed PDFs where required.
- Decision Objects & Approval Workflow (Core): Expose decision cards and their options, comments, and audit trails as sources for the export.
- Error Handling & Validation: Centralized messaging for export configuration errors, validation of selections, and recovery UI in-case of failures.
- Branding & Custom Client Links: Ability to apply studio branding to client-facing export links and PDFs (logo, colors, optional custom domain).
- Decision Log PDF Template: Brandable HTML/CSS template that renders a high-quality PDF with a cover page, option visuals, audit log, and attachments appendix.
- Success / Confirmation Page: Show after successful exports or client approvals with status and next steps.
- Decision Detail Page: Full view for a single Decision Card with options, the audit trail, attachments, and actions (share, export, create follow-up task).
- Loading / Processing Page: Global loading state during background operations like export generation and large uploads.

Visual guidance:
- Use a clean, calm workspace with generous whitespace, clear typographic hierarchy, and a strong emphasis on content over chrome.
- Maintain consistent branding across PDF exports, client-facing links, and on-page UI elements.

